# music-content-models

Core data models for managing music industry content and metadata:

## Artist Model
Importance Score: 95

Key Components:
- Industry standard identifier mappings (Spotify ID, Apple Music ID, MusicBrainz ID)
- Genre taxonomy with weighted relevance scoring
- Social platform identity resolution (Instagram, Twitter, TikTok handles)
- Geographic market associations and primary location data
- Distribution platform state tracking

## Release Model 
Importance Score: 90

Key Components:
- ISRC/UPC code management and validation
- Multi-format release configurations (album, EP, single)
- Platform-specific metadata requirements
- Distribution state machine (draft, submitted, live, taken-down)
- Release window scheduling with timezone handling
- Pre-save campaign configuration

## Event Model
Importance Score: 85

Key Components:
- Venue capacity and ticket tier management
- Support act and headliner relationships
- Event type categorization (concert, festival, tour date)
- Geographic market metadata
- Pre-sale and public sale scheduling
- Box office integration points

The core business value lies in the industry-specific metadata handling and platform integrations, particularly around:
- Standard music identifiers (ISRC/UPC)
- Distribution workflow states
- Platform-specific requirements
- Artist/release relationships
- Event capacity management

